                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="60175" author="luke" created="Tue, 2 Nov 2010 05:20:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added call to reset() before invoking the filter chain.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="60591" author="astefan" created="Thu, 11 Nov 2010 22:11:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Two potential workarounds:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) Use anonymous attributes for the unsecured resources instead of filters=&quot;none&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
2) Add a filter after the security filters with the following doFIlter method:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public void doFilter(ServletRequest request, ServletResponse response, FilterChain chain)&lt;br/&gt;
throws IOException, ServletException {&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;while (request instanceof ServletRequestWrapper) {&lt;br/&gt;
if (request instanceof FirewalledRequest) &lt;/p&gt;
{ ((FirewalledRequest)request).reset(); break; }
&lt;p&gt;request = ((ServletRequestWrapper)request).getRequest();&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
